WEBVTT

00:05:59.160 --> 00:06:02.496
and that you are probably
a better multitasker.

00:06:02.520 --> 00:06:05.936
And these are factors that set in early,

00:06:05.960 --> 00:06:07.896
and so that ought to give you some sense

00:06:07.920 --> 00:06:12.456
of when to give junior or juniorette
lessons in another language.

00:06:12.480 --> 00:06:14.896
Bilingualism is healthy.

00:06:14.920 --> 00:06:16.816
And then, third --

00:06:16.840 --> 00:06:20.240
languages are just an awful lot of fun.

00:06:20.800 --> 00:06:22.536
Much more fun than we're often told.

00:06:22.560 --> 00:06:25.856
So for example,
Arabic: "kataba," he wrote,

00:06:25.880 --> 00:06:29.096
"yaktubu," he writes, she writes.

00:06:29.120 --> 00:06:32.136
"Uktub," write, in the imperative.